Shell Norco Chemical Plant - East Site
Norco Chemical Plant - East Site
Risk Management Plan (RMP) - Executive Summary

Shell operates a Norco Chemical Plant (or NCP)- East Site located in Norco, LA.  This summary
provides an overview of various RMP activities at Equilon, including the following:
- The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source;
- The stationary source and regulated substances handled;
- The general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps;
- The five-year accident history;
- The emergency response program; and
- Planned changes to improve safety.

THE ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES AT THE STATIONARY SOURCE
Shell complies with the OSHA Process Safety Management for highly hazardous chemicals standards. The site has programs in place to ensure proper operation and maintenance of process systems. All operators are properly trained and are knowledgeable in the safe operation of the system. The equipment and piping at this facility has been designed and constructed using good engineering practices and to conform to industry standards. Norco has established an HSSE management system to help ensure safe operation of the processes that includes the prevention of accidental releases of hazardous substances. One component of this system is a risk management program (RMP) that provides a basis for managing risks at the facility. The RMP complies with the requirements of the Environmental Protection Agency's (EPA's) regulation 40 CFR part 68 and the Occupational Safety & Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management (PSM) standard 29 CFR 1910.119.

THE STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES HANDLED

The following is a list of RMP toxic and flammable substances stored at the NCP - East Site:

Flammables:
-  Acetylene;
-  Hydrogen;
-  Butene;
-  1,3 Butadiene;
-  Ethane;
-  Ethylene;
-  Propylene;
-  Propane;
-  Multiple Flammable Mixtures
